modules.description: Matches strings against a regular expression pattern. Accepts a compiled Str.regexp and applies it to input strings for validation or extraction. Used to parse URL paths by matching against predefined route patterns.

This module offers operations for managing maps with string keys and arbitrary values, including insertion, deletion, lookup, and set-like manipulations such as union and intersection. It supports advanced transformations like predicate-based searches, value mapping, and splitting maps, along with strict and optional handling of bindings. Use cases include configuration management, data aggregation, and processing structured datasets requiring efficient key-value operations.

Checks if a key exists in a map of string-to-value pairs and retrieves values based on keys. Operates on a map structure where keys are strings and values are of an abstract type. Used to access configuration parameters or request-specific data within a processing context.

Extracts substrings based on index, reads files into lists or single strings, pads integers with leading zeros or spaces, and generates timestamp strings. Operates on strings, integers, and file paths. Useful for parsing log entries, formatting numerical data, and generating time-stamped filenames.

Provides operations to construct and convert verb representations from and to strings. Works with an abstract type `t` encapsulating verb data. Used to standardize verb forms in natural language processing tasks.

Provides functions to extract query parameters and path segments from HTTP requests. Operates on strings representing URL components. Used to parse and isolate specific parts of a request for routing or data extraction.

Provides operations for managing string-keyed maps with arbitrary values, including insertion, deletion, lookup, set operations, and advanced transformations like mapping, filtering, and splitting. Supports key existence checks and value retrieval from abstract-type maps, enabling efficient data access and manipulation. Users can perform configuration management, data aggregation, and structured dataset processing with precise control over key-value relationships. Examples include extracting specific configuration parameters or combining multiple maps through union or intersection.

Provides string matching and parsing capabilities using compiled regular expressions. Accepts a regexp and input string to validate, extract, or route requests based on pattern matching. Enables precise control over string analysis and transformation. Can be used to parse URL paths by applying predefined route patterns.

Provides functions for parsing and validating JSON Web Tokens, extracting claims, and verifying signatures using HMAC-SHA algorithms. Operates on strings representing tokens and maps containing decoded payload data. Used to authenticate user requests in API endpoints by verifying token validity and extracting user identifiers.

Combines string manipulation, data extraction, and transformation utilities for processing logs, URLs, and configuration data. Supports operations like substring extraction, verb normalization, query parsing, and map management, with functions for padding, timestamp generation, and regex-based matching. Enables tasks such as isolating route parameters, standardizing linguistic data, and managing key-value stores. Examples include parsing HTTP request components, generating timestamped filenames, and extracting configuration values.
